  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The proposed development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the proposals contained in the application and the plans submitted ( 15BC/P/010; Planning Statement Dated 30th September 2021. Received: 14/10/2021.\r\n15BC/P100 Rev: A; 15BC/P101 Rev: A; 15BC/P102; 15BC/P103;15BC/P104; 15BC/P200 Rev: A; \r\n15BC/P201 Rev: A; 15BC/P202; 15BC/P203; 15BC/P204; 15BC/F/200 Rev: A; 15BC/F/201 Rev: A. \r\nReceived: 21/10/2021.\r\nEmail from Aun Qurashi (LBH) to Sam Smith (LBH) dated 16/12/2021 at 20:51 with subject RE: 15 Bedfont Close - P/2021/4092. Received: 17/12/2021. ) therewith and approved by the Local Planning Authority, or as shall have been otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority before the building is used.",
    "Condition : 2 - The building known as \"15 Bedfont Close, Feltham, TW14 8LJ\" shall not be occupied by more than one person in receipt of care at a time.",
    "Condition : 3 - Within six months of the date of this permission, details of noise mitigation measures to minimise noise to the adjoining property at 13 Bedfont Close in accordance with British Standard BS8233:2014, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. \r\nThe development shall thereafter be implemented in full accordance approved details within three months of the approval of details pursuant to this condition and thereafter maintained for the lifetime of the development.\r\n",
    "Condition : 4 - Within six months of the date of this permission, details of one secure and covered cycle parking space, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. \r\nThe development shall thereafter be implemented in full accordance approved details within three months of the approval of details pursuant to this condition and thereafter maintained for the lifetime of the development.\r\n",
    "Condition : 5 - Within six months of the date of this permission, details of a Workplace Travel Plan prepared in accordance with up to date TfL Travel Plan Guidance, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. \r\nThe development shall thereafter be implemented and operated in full accordance approved details for the lifetime of the development.\r\n",
    "Condition : 6 - Within six months of the date of this permission, full details of Waste and Recycling provision, including storage and collection arrangements, including for any clinical waste, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. \r\nThe development shall thereafter be implemented in full accordance approved details within three months of the approval of details pursuant to this condition and thereafter maintained for the lifetime of the development.\r\n",
    "Condition : 7 - The premises shall be used as 'Residential accommodation and care to people in need of care' only and for no other purpose (including any other purpose in Class C2 of the Schedule to the Town and Country Planning (Use Classes) Order 1987 (as amended), nor in any provision equivalent to that Class in any statutory instrument revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification"
  ],
